AS an another American I must say,WE THE PEOPLE IN ORDER TO FORM A MORE PERFECT UNION,must respect each other and learn that through cooperation will make OUR COUNTRY a place that shall make even the smallest feel safe.My name is Daniel Louis Knight,served in VIETNAM from 1966 to 1972,I went there to hopefully help the VIETNAMESE gain the freedom to decide there future,for this I am loosing my life,agent-orange is my vehicle to beyond.Am happy for getting this computer and the Internet,two finger's and time.WE as a people must listen to all,when we allow fear and ignorence to alter and control our emotion's,WE loose the essence of our collective as a nation and become a product of isolation,I can tell you about that,it only leaves one empty and vulnerable,we are more than that,we are a people who are big enough to say&quot;I'm Sorry&quot; and small enough to &quot;Look Up&quot;,WE are WE,we make mistakes and then we make great progress,I used to feel angry and guilty,one day I woke up and decided that there had to be another path,there is and it is sure a much more productive and a living one,for me time is important,too much so that it be filled with meaningfull things,like my Children &amp; Grandchildren,building for a future,I truly hope that we can come togather and take the time to listen,when we do this we will learn how to build a better tomorrow and notice the truth about today,just on the news last night that most PEOPLE in IRAN like US and the&quot;OUR U.S.A.&quot;,Take care out there my fellow American's,dream a new dream,dance to a new tune,sing a new song,&quot;OK&quot;Let US get along!!! 
